Class Summary
Class Description
Fly
Contains several methods that aid in the
display and movement of Mosca
FlyWorld
Contains information about the world (i.e., the grid of squares)
and handles most of the game play work that is NOT GUI specific
FlyWorldGUI
Handles all the work to setup the GUI
and dealing with keystrokes, specifically the arrows
DO NOT modify any code in this file
Frog
Handles display, movement, and fly eating capabalities for frogs
GridLocation
Represents a single grid location (i.e., one row/column position) Within a 2D grid in a Graphical User Interface (GUI)
